rComments: His lectures are not heavy with material. He tells very long stories about his life that applies to the theory we are talking about. Honestly, I got a lot of other homework done during his class. Just pay attention to the classes before exams because he drops a ton of hints.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: This man couldn't talk about course material if his life depended on it. Honestly the only reason to take this class is because its an easy A. Get the textbook, go to the review sessions and read the short answer sample questions (as 1 from each chapter is on the test). I usually just showed up to sign the attendance sheet and get the easy 10%

Dr. Wall is hilarious although he goes off topic during lectures very often. Do the questions he provides you b/c it will really help you in doing well for the midterm and final. Attendance is mandatory and every time you didnt come to class a percentage will be taken off from a total of 10%. Labs usually dont take the full hour.

OK yes he goes on many tangents but this is one of the only moments you will have in university where the road to an A+ is clear without any traps. You go to class, you study what he says to and BOOM you get a good grade. All Uni classes should be like that.
Easy marker and gives you the exam questions to memorize so it's pretty hard to do badly in the class. He goes off topic a lot during lectures and got mad once when someone didn't address him by DR.
This professor is fair and cares about the students and their success. There are no surprises on the exams. Follow his instructions and you will do great.

This class is a really easy A+ if you study the slides (or read the book). For someone who does not sleep much, I appreciate his monotone voice as it prepares me for a good night rest (no, I am not sarcastic, folks). Theres one midterm and one final - he will also give you 15 long questions to memorize in order to get 100% on the writing portion.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Overall, this class is easy; Easy material and exams especially because he has such clear expectations. Unfortunately his classes are mind-numbingly boring. He has his moments, but he talks SO much. He goes on so many tangents and it is such a waste of time. Could def get away with a good grade and not going but attendance can affect your grade.
Honestly he's a very nice guy ! He just goes off topic a lot which makes the lectures last longer and I think that's why ppl don't show up. The material is pretty straightforward.

One of the worst profs I have ever had; so off topic it's unbelievable. He was on a slide about "How Peers Influence Adolescents" so naturally he talks about the American Constitution for 20 min. To make matters worse, he writes on the syllabus that the text is available online, and then when you go to study for the midterm you find out it isn't.

Just don't do it. Hated every minute being in that classroom - attendance was mandatory. Get ready to teach yourself this whole course. Read off chapter summaries and skipped around with powerpoints made from god knows when. I had no idea what I was learning since he went off topic, mainly human rights issues (?). Have a background in neuroscience.

Basically, we had to listen to a 60yr old guy ramble on human rights and the disease model of addiction for 3 months. (Obviously both topics were not on the final exam, seeing as this was a course on pharmacology/psychology).

The worst prof I have ever had at uO. He rambles off topic, you never know what to take notes on, and he skips around during lectures between random powerpoints and having storytime with the textbook chapter summaries. He apparently has a neuro background but could never answer Qs brought up in class so have fun teaching yourself the entire course!

He talks about anything but the subject itself and then expects us to learn it all by ourselves. I thought myself the whole class, even though I went to all his classes since they are mandatory. He is incredibly boring, off topic and quotes Pink Floyd songs (so if you like Pink Floyd, you got that going for you).

Very down to earth professor, I personally enjoyed his class a lot. Every now and tends to crack some funny joke. Very predictable exams which take away the stress while studying. I would recommend him!
I think attendance is mandatory so he can have a captive audience. Otherwise I doubt people would show up; he is just that boring.

I am sure he is a great man but in all honesty I stopped going to class half way through the first lecture. If you know anyone who has insomnia or any sleeping disorder really, just put on a recording of this man's voice and they will be asleep before you know it. All in all 10/10 would teach myself everything again
Really easy exams but lectures are mandatory but he rants so much about his personal life...

Excellent prof. Only 1 midterm and 1 final exam, 6 chapters each. Both exams are half or more MC questions, and his SA questions require some memorization. He told us there would be 6 SA questions and gave the 18 possible ones to the class. He will bump up your grade if you are off by a little, as long as you attend class. He made it easy for us.

Very down to earth. Tests are multiple choice and a few short answers. Read the textbok twice and you'll do great. You don't necessarily need to show up for class, but it is useful to attend since he does provide hints for the exams. Only 2 exams: a midterm (40%) and a final (60%). He seems to enjoy his professor career and his students. Smard lad.

Unlike other raters, I thought Professor Wall was an extremely clear and straight forward educator! His tests were simple if you read the textbook and slides; no surprise questions! He follows up material with his personal life stories which are not only hilarious but, help you remember the material better. He does not give surprise questions!

Very dry lectures, he rambles on and on, plus he isn't clear about what's on the exams. He also doesn't allow you to use acronyms for drugs and receptors. Wth is the point of that? Also says that exam will be easy when it's nowhere near that. Know the anatomy REALLY well because he asks for the most obscure parts you can think of. Avoid.

Monotonous. Unclear. Gave outlines during review sessions of what to/not to study and completely ignored them for the exams, then insisted we were lying when we contested it. Promised review docs and never gave. Mandatory attendance. Goes on a million different tangents and repeats himself. Essentially repeats the textbook. AVOID HIM.

Definitely know the things he goes over in review classes, but be prepared to need to know more than that too (even if he says not to). Lectures are very boring but attendance is mandatory. If you put in the time you can get an A+ since everything is just out of the textbook, but it's a loooooot of memorizing.

One of the most dreadful profs I've had in psychology. Lectures are very boring and the prof makes many mistakes/contradictions, requires you to memorize drug names instead of acronyms, lies about exam content. He won't tell you that he'll test you on very specific and cryptic details of the human brain anatomy, so be prepared. Or just drop like me
Great professor!

He was VERY tangential making class drag on, normally I find tangents entertaining but I found he would just repeat himself over and over. Class is almost painful. I gave him a 3 for clarity because before the final he went through the slides and deleted what we didn't have to know. Memorize what is left and you'll do fine, at least I did.

Professor Wall spends the majority of his class time talking about himself. You rely fully on the textbook to learn about the course; he does not even understand some of the concepts he's teaching. He does give useful hints about exams, but you could go the whole semester without attending his class. Just read the book.

Had to teach myself pretty much the entire course. Isn't very clear in explaining things to students without a strong background in science. Has multiple slide-sets for each lecture and bounces back and forth through them, making it nearly impossible to keep up. Take note of diagrams he tells you to learn; they are definitely on the exam.

Did not enjoy this professor. He rambles a lot and goes off topic, and doesn't really seem to know anything about the subject. Was disappointed with his class, but you can still get a good mark if you read the textbook on your own.

I really enjoyed this prof's class.  He is very enthusiastic about the topic, and extremely knowledgeable.  He does tend to "ramble" a bit, but I found it was usually entertaining.  If you read the texts and go to class, you can get an A-, if you really read the texts and study hard, you can get an A+.
